WEBVTT

1
00:00:54.082 --> 00:00:56.084
White's dead body!

2
00:00:57.819 --> 00:00:59.555
My goodness!

3
00:01:05.827 --> 00:01:07.696
This was not
in my tarot reading for today.

4
00:01:07.796 --> 00:01:09.531
Kind of metal. though.

5
00:01:12.868 --> 00:01:15.036
Ow!

6
00:01:17.472 --> 00:01:18.974
Ah.

7
00:01:19.074 --> 00:01:20.508
Whoa!

8
00:01:25.747 --> 00:01:27.115
What are you gonna
do about this?

9
00:01:27.215 --> 00:01:28.416
Uh. me?

10
00:01:28.516 --> 00:01:29.551
Why me?

11
00:01:29.651 --> 00:01:30.886
You're the captain.

12
00:01:30.986 --> 00:01:33.121
Oh. uh. yeah. Of course.

13
00:01:33.221 --> 00:01:34.322
I'm the captain.

14
00:01:34.422 --> 00:01:36.792
- We should call MIRA.
- The comms are down.

15
00:01:36.892 --> 00:01:39.194
Remember the serious
but kind of sexy robot voice?

16
00:01:39.294 --> 00:01:40.495
Oh. uh...

17
00:01:40.596 --> 00:01:42.363
Non-emergency meeting.

18
00:01:42.463 --> 00:01:43.765
Non-emergency meeting.

19
00:01:45.734 --> 00:01:46.968
This is your captain speaking.

20
00:01:47.068 --> 00:01:48.970
There is no need for alarm.

21
00:01:51.072 --> 00:01:52.941
Where's Blue?

22
00:01:53.041 --> 00:01:54.409
- Yeah. where's Blue?
- We love Blue.

23
00:01:54.509 --> 00:01:56.044
I trust Blue more
than any of ya.

24
00:01:56.144 --> 00:01:57.946
- but trust is a construct.
- If only there was

25
00:01:58.046 --> 00:01:59.581
someone smart and capable
with impeccable bone structure

26
00:01:59.681 --> 00:02:01.116
who could take charge.

27
00:02:01.240 --> 00:02:03.795
Subtitle Sync by: Aren Zohrabi

28
00:02:03.919 --> 00:02:04.886
I'm here.

29
00:02:04.986 --> 00:02:06.622
Yeah.

30
00:02:06.722 --> 00:02:08.356
- Great. What else?
- Yeah.

31
00:02:08.456 --> 00:02:10.759
Oh. God.

32
00:02:10.859 --> 00:02:12.928
It never gets any easier.

33
00:02:13.028 --> 00:02:14.863
Well. technically.
it should be easier

34
00:02:14.963 --> 00:02:16.965
'cause you're only lifting
half the weight.

35
00:02:18.767 --> 00:02:20.201
Now. hold on there.

36
00:02:20.301 --> 00:02:22.170
We can't have just everyone
hanging around MedBay.

37
00:02:22.270 --> 00:02:24.539
If you're gonna hang around.
you should. uh.

38
00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:26.274
hang around the cafeteria.

39
00:02:26.374 --> 00:02:28.143
At least until we sort this out.

40
00:02:28.243 --> 00:02:30.812
Until I sort this out.
I'm the captain.

41
00:02:32.948 --> 00:02:35.917
The dead have stories to tell.

42
00:02:36.017 --> 00:02:39.287
but they have to give everything
up to finally be heard.

43
00:02:42.891 --> 00:02:44.960
It's a standard
liability waiver.

44
00:02:45.060 --> 00:02:46.895
They were definitely going to
sign it after the pizza party.

45
00:02:46.995 --> 00:02:48.463
Probably. Don't worry about it.

46
00:02:48.563 --> 00:02:50.498
This is just
a normal accident. right?

47
00:02:50.598 --> 00:02:52.734
Hey. this kind of thing happens
all the time.

48
00:02:52.834 --> 00:02:54.903
Folks splitting mysteriously
in twain?

49
00:02:55.003 --> 00:02:56.872
No. mysterious twain-splitting

50
00:02:56.972 --> 00:02:58.740
is actually quite rare.

51
00:02:58.840 --> 00:03:02.243
I'll have to run some intensive
tests to find out what happened.

52
00:03:07.515 --> 00:03:09.317
I thought leaving the worm farm
would get me away

53
00:03:09.417 --> 00:03:11.252
from horrible
equipment manglings.

54
00:03:11.352 --> 00:03:13.221
That was no equipment mangling.
if you ask me.

55
00:03:13.321 --> 00:03:14.990
I've seen all kinds
of workplace injuries.

56
00:03:15.090 --> 00:03:16.591
and that was something else.

57
00:03:16.692 --> 00:03:17.893
Definitely something else.

58
00:03:17.993 --> 00:03:19.494
I hear ya. big dog.

59
00:03:19.594 --> 00:03:22.964
Rumor has it White took
the steering wheel from Green.

60
00:03:23.064 --> 00:03:25.901
It's Green's lifelong dream.
Just couldn't handle it.

61
00:03:26.001 --> 00:03:28.403
They snapped! It drove 'em
into crazy bloodlust.

62
00:03:28.503 --> 00:03:30.171
- Hmm.
I never considered that.
- Sure...

63
00:03:30.271 --> 00:03:32.573
I don't have lust for anything.
least of all blood.

64
00:03:32.674 --> 00:03:35.110
Where did you hear
this provocative rumor?

65
00:03:35.210 --> 00:03:38.213
Well. I started it.
I just thought it'd be funny.

66
00:03:38.313 --> 00:03:39.514
And it is.

67
00:03:39.614 --> 00:03:41.717
I still think
it's probably true.

68
00:03:59.567 --> 00:04:01.002
I see.

69
00:04:01.102 --> 00:04:03.905
So. um. is White dead?

70
00:04:04.005 --> 00:04:06.107
Yes. White is very dead.

71
00:04:06.207 --> 00:04:07.608
- Oh. no.
- Fun reminder.

72
00:04:07.709 --> 00:04:08.910
Death is a preexisting condition

73
00:04:09.010 --> 00:04:10.611
not covered
by MIRA health insurance.

74
00:04:10.712 --> 00:04:12.613
I'm worried about something
bigger than death.

75
00:04:12.714 --> 00:04:14.015
Demotion?

76
00:04:14.115 --> 00:04:15.550
In this case. I'm referring

77
00:04:15.650 --> 00:04:17.185
to a pink organic residue

78
00:04:17.285 --> 00:04:19.554
found on the two halves
of White's body.

79
00:04:19.654 --> 00:04:21.422
Mm. yes.

80
00:04:21.522 --> 00:04:23.658
I believe that's called...
<i>bluud.</i>

81
00:04:23.759 --> 00:04:27.328
Yes. that could explain it.
but that's not exactly

82
00:04:27.428 --> 00:04:29.497
what I'm talking about
right now. sport.

83
00:04:29.597 --> 00:04:31.767
I think we need to scan
all of the crewmates

84
00:04:31.867 --> 00:04:33.401
to see
if we can find the origin.

85
00:04:33.501 --> 00:04:35.370
Maybe it was something
White brought on board.

86
00:04:35.470 --> 00:04:38.206
but if it was something
they picked up on the ship.

87
00:04:38.306 --> 00:04:40.575
then the crew might be
in danger.

88
00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:44.913
That sounds like
it could cause a lot of panic.

89
00:04:45.013 --> 00:04:46.915
How would that reflect
on my leadership?

90
00:04:47.015 --> 00:04:49.684
- Poorly.
- Well. I don't like that.

91
00:04:49.785 --> 00:04:52.353
The alternative is
we do nothing. which could mean

92
00:04:52.453 --> 00:04:56.124
that more crewmates suffer
horrible and graphic deaths.

93
00:04:56.925 --> 00:04:58.960
Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

94
00:04:59.060 --> 00:05:02.330
Hmm. Mm-mm. Mm-mm. No. no. no.

95
00:05:02.430 --> 00:05:05.901
Uh. hmm. Hmm.

96
00:05:06.001 --> 00:05:08.003
No. no. I'll take care of this.

97
00:05:08.103 --> 00:05:10.171
Hello. everyone.
This is your captain speaking.

98
00:05:10.271 --> 00:05:12.573
I. with minimal help from Blue.

99
00:05:12.673 --> 00:05:15.276
have finished my initial study
of the situation

100
00:05:15.376 --> 00:05:18.013
and determined
everything is completely fine.

101
00:05:18.113 --> 00:05:19.981
White passed away peacefully

102
00:05:20.081 --> 00:05:21.516
from a mysterious
industrial accident.

103
00:05:21.616 --> 00:05:23.318
- Bless the stars.
- It's good to know.

104
00:05:23.418 --> 00:05:25.220
LIME
That's what they want you
to think.

105
00:05:25.320 --> 00:05:26.888
But you all must report
to MedBay for mandatory

106
00:05:26.988 --> 00:05:28.723
and possibly invasive
body scans.

107
00:05:28.824 --> 00:05:30.158
What? Oh.

108
00:05:30.258 --> 00:05:32.260
That doesn't sound very natural.

109
00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:34.762
Well. I just got mine.
and I feel totally great.

110
00:05:36.497 --> 00:05:39.267
So. th-that's all you're going
to tell us about White?

111
00:05:39.367 --> 00:05:41.436
Who?

112
00:05:42.403 --> 00:05:45.841
Oh. uh. uh. n-no. no. no.

113
00:05:45.941 --> 00:05:47.575
Uh. privacy laws.
bureaucracy. something.

114
00:05:47.675 --> 00:05:49.510
something. something.
blah. blah. blah. blah. blah.

115
00:05:49.610 --> 00:05:52.047
No way in hell I'm gonna be
scanned. documented.

116
00:05:52.147 --> 00:05:53.581
and registered
in my government name.

117
00:05:53.681 --> 00:05:56.317
If you want to have photons
blasted into your bone

118
00:05:56.417 --> 00:05:59.654
until you pick up radio waves.
be my guest.

119
00:05:59.754 --> 00:06:02.357
but I'm keeping this body
a temple.

120
00:06:03.424 --> 00:06:04.926
Still don't like it.

121
00:06:05.026 --> 00:06:06.627
but Brown and I already made
the deductible

122
00:06:06.727 --> 00:06:09.397
on our union insurance. so go
hog wild with the tests. baby!

123
00:06:09.497 --> 00:06:10.932
Union.

124
00:06:11.032 --> 00:06:13.301
Union.

125
00:06:13.401 --> 00:06:15.170
- Who's in your union?
- Just me and Brown.

126
00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:16.371
You're married?

127
00:06:16.471 --> 00:06:17.805
No. No one's married here.

128
00:06:17.906 --> 00:06:19.140
No one is ever getting married.

129
00:06:19.240 --> 00:06:20.876
All of you lonely.
unmarried crewmates.

130
00:06:20.976 --> 00:06:22.543
get back to your tasks.

131
00:06:22.643 --> 00:06:24.045
Speaking of lonely.

132
00:06:24.145 --> 00:06:25.613
where's Purple?

133
00:06:27.916 --> 00:06:30.251
Uh. okay. okay...

134
00:06:31.752 --> 00:06:33.654
Hey! Working hard
or hardly working?

135
00:06:33.754 --> 00:06:36.191
I can't find
any footage of White.

136
00:06:36.291 --> 00:06:39.060
Like I told you earlier.
these cameras don't record.

137
00:06:39.160 --> 00:06:40.628
They're only in black and white.

138
00:06:40.728 --> 00:06:42.030
They're completely useless.

139
00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:44.199
Yo. Purple. you're up next!

140
00:06:44.299 --> 00:06:46.167
Scan time!

141
00:06:46.267 --> 00:06:48.536
- Scan?
- A possibly invasive
body scan.

142
00:06:48.636 --> 00:06:50.038
Uh. fine.

143
00:06:50.138 --> 00:06:51.706
I'll just drop
everything I'm doing.

144
00:06:51.806 --> 00:06:53.508
Since nobody else here cares
about the safety of the crew.

145
00:06:53.608 --> 00:06:54.642
why should I?

146
00:06:55.810 --> 00:06:57.378
I won't know
what I'm dealing with

147
00:06:57.478 --> 00:07:00.348
until I can develop and compare
everyone's scans.

148
00:07:00.448 --> 00:07:01.516
Is it disease?

149
00:07:01.616 --> 00:07:02.884
A new bacteria?

150
00:07:02.984 --> 00:07:04.419
An unknown mutation?

151
00:07:04.519 --> 00:07:08.089
Until I know that every crewmate
on this ship is safe.

152
00:07:08.189 --> 00:07:10.291
I won't sleep a wink.

153
00:07:11.092 --> 00:07:12.860
Swoon!

154
00:07:12.961 --> 00:07:14.129
Is-is this okay?

155
00:07:14.229 --> 00:07:15.630
I can stand stiller.

156
00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:16.932
I can stand <i>really</i> still.

157
00:07:17.032 --> 00:07:18.733
You're doing just fine.

158
00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:19.867
Thanks.

159
00:07:19.968 --> 00:07:21.536
I'm just nervous.

160
00:07:21.636 --> 00:07:24.205
To be honest. sometimes it feels
like I shouldn't even be here.

161
00:07:24.305 --> 00:07:25.773
Where else would you be?

162
00:07:25.873 --> 00:07:27.976
Back at home. Farming?

163
00:07:28.076 --> 00:07:31.179
I mean. how am I supposed to go
from assistant worm herder

164
00:07:31.279 --> 00:07:34.049
to unpaid spaceship intern
to paid heroic captain?

165
00:07:34.149 --> 00:07:35.850
We all take different paths.

166
00:07:35.951 --> 00:07:39.554
My first doctorate was in
the history of elegiac poetry.

167
00:07:39.654 --> 00:07:41.289
Once I understood
the beauty of life.

168
00:07:41.389 --> 00:07:44.759
I decided to pursue medicine
so I could also save it.

169
00:07:44.859 --> 00:07:46.094
Trust your heart.

170
00:07:46.194 --> 00:07:47.562
It will never steer you wrong.

171
00:07:47.662 --> 00:07:49.764
Swoon.

172
00:07:50.731 --> 00:07:53.901
Oh. no. Some ore got cracked.

173
00:07:54.002 --> 00:07:55.503
We'll have to contain
the energy.

174
00:07:55.603 --> 00:07:57.272
Uh. I'll need salt
to make a circle.

175
00:07:57.372 --> 00:07:58.806
and I think
my crystal kit has some--

176
00:07:58.906 --> 00:08:00.075
Wrong kind of energy.

177
00:08:00.175 --> 00:08:01.409
It's just fuel.

178
00:08:01.509 --> 00:08:04.245
What are you doing here?

179
00:08:04.345 --> 00:08:06.147
Just here to check on our crew.

180
00:08:06.247 --> 00:08:07.882
the most valuable resource
we have!

181
00:08:07.983 --> 00:08:10.351
Well. after the Ore-Plus.

182
00:08:10.451 --> 00:08:11.987
And the raw materials
of the ship.

183
00:08:12.087 --> 00:08:13.054
And this clipboard.

184
00:08:13.154 --> 00:08:14.389
So-so I just want to make sure

185
00:08:14.489 --> 00:08:16.391
you two are
emotionally taken care of.

186
00:08:16.491 --> 00:08:18.859
So you can physically take care
of the product.

187
00:08:18.960 --> 00:08:20.061
Huh?

188
00:08:20.828 --> 00:08:23.231
I'm sorry. I'm looking.
but I can't find Lime anywhere.

189
00:08:23.331 --> 00:08:25.233
Black.
can you get scanned instead

190
00:08:25.333 --> 00:08:26.767
so I don't get yelled at?

191
00:08:32.673 --> 00:08:34.775
Wow. your equipment is so new.

192
00:08:34.875 --> 00:08:37.912
All MIRA gave me is a crappy
microscope I have no use for.

193
00:08:38.013 --> 00:08:41.049
I find that many of the sciences
are underfunded.

194
00:08:41.149 --> 00:08:42.317
Everyone wants to give money

195
00:08:42.417 --> 00:08:44.819
to some abstract concept
of "innovation."

196
00:08:44.919 --> 00:08:47.788
but they rarely want
to put in the work and financing

197
00:08:47.888 --> 00:08:51.059
towards a better understanding
of our world.

198
00:08:53.928 --> 00:08:55.696
BLACK
Swoon.

199
00:09:02.370 --> 00:09:05.106
I hope your scanner
can see through my aura.

200
00:09:05.206 --> 00:09:06.874
It's pretty dark today.

201
00:09:06.974 --> 00:09:09.344
I'm sure you don't believe
in all that.

202
00:09:09.444 --> 00:09:10.945
Quite the contrary.

203
00:09:11.046 --> 00:09:12.780
While my job
is to heal the physical.

204
00:09:12.880 --> 00:09:15.716
I think it's just as important
to heal the soul.

205
00:09:15.816 --> 00:09:18.786
Healing travels
across many planes.

206
00:09:19.787 --> 00:09:21.522
Swoon.

207
00:09:27.728 --> 00:09:30.265
I hate to be a stickler.
but have you taken care of--

208
00:09:30.365 --> 00:09:33.834
The 422 pages of paperwork
I've already notarized?

209
00:09:35.503 --> 00:09:38.539
- What a dreamboat.
- Um. what a dreamboat.

210
00:09:39.407 --> 00:09:41.942
CYAN and ORANGE:
Swoon...!

211
00:09:42.043 --> 00:09:44.045
Now for Lime.

212
00:09:44.145 --> 00:09:47.715
I hate to compromise my ethics
by fooling a patient. but...

213
00:09:47.815 --> 00:09:50.851
And now it's time to look
a gremlin right in the eye!

214
00:09:50.951 --> 00:09:52.987
Don't do it!
You'll fall in love!

215
00:09:53.088 --> 00:09:54.122
You scared it away.

216
00:09:54.222 --> 00:09:55.656
Thank you for saving me.

217
00:09:55.756 --> 00:09:57.625
You're welcome.
Love and peace. big dog.

218
00:09:57.725 --> 00:09:59.760
While I have you here.
would you mind taking your scan?

219
00:09:59.860 --> 00:10:01.662
You can't scan me!
I know my rights!

220
00:10:01.762 --> 00:10:04.365
That machine will steal my DNA.
sell it to marauders

221
00:10:04.465 --> 00:10:06.501
and they'll use it
as a map to my organs!

222
00:10:06.601 --> 00:10:08.303
Now. I'll be the first to admit

223
00:10:08.403 --> 00:10:11.206
that the medical community
has a lot to apologize for.

224
00:10:11.306 --> 00:10:12.707
I'm sorry. Lime.

225
00:10:15.076 --> 00:10:17.645
Lime. I know you have
your personal beliefs.

226
00:10:17.745 --> 00:10:19.647
but this is bigger
than you or me.

227
00:10:19.747 --> 00:10:22.283
I really need a scan
of every crewmate.

228
00:10:22.383 --> 00:10:24.885
I know it's hard
to open your heart to trust

229
00:10:24.985 --> 00:10:27.255
in this crazy. mixed-up world.

230
00:10:27.355 --> 00:10:29.056
Just this once...

231
00:10:29.157 --> 00:10:31.492
can you trust me?

232
00:10:32.393 --> 00:10:34.028
Fine! Swoon. swoon. swoon!

233
00:10:34.129 --> 00:10:36.264
But I'm watching you shred
my scans when you're finished.

234
00:10:36.364 --> 00:10:38.032
We'll do it...

235
00:10:38.133 --> 00:10:39.767
together.

236
00:10:52.147 --> 00:10:53.981
<i>Hour 26.</i>

237
00:10:54.081 --> 00:10:56.184
I normally advocate for
a healthy work-and-life balance

238
00:10:56.284 --> 00:10:58.253
for my patients.
but extraordinary circumstances

239
00:10:58.353 --> 00:11:00.655
require
extraordinary sacrifices.

240
00:11:00.755 --> 00:11:03.358
Hmm. There's something
I must be missing.

241
00:11:03.458 --> 00:11:06.427
Crewmates don't just
mysteriously split in twain.

242
00:11:06.527 --> 00:11:08.663
And with
that pink organic residue.

243
00:11:08.763 --> 00:11:10.198
I have a hard time
believing it to be

244
00:11:10.298 --> 00:11:12.333
a normal workplace accident.

245
00:11:12.433 --> 00:11:13.534
I just need...

246
00:11:19.907 --> 00:11:21.776
Okay. Okay.

247
00:11:21.876 --> 00:11:24.545
This is normal. This is...

248
00:11:24.645 --> 00:11:25.613
Wait.

249
00:11:25.713 --> 00:11:27.682
What's this?

250
00:11:33.888 --> 00:11:34.922
Uh...

251
00:11:45.266 --> 00:11:49.370
"And. lo. the knowledge
of thy sin be found.

252
00:11:49.470 --> 00:11:54.242
the curse of blessing
leaves the loss profound."

253
00:12:44.825 --> 00:12:46.927
Keybot. Keybot. Keybot. Keybot.

254
00:12:47.027 --> 00:12:49.230
Chirp.
